(201, 'Toronto App FIIX Could Change the Way You Get Your Car Serviced', 'toronto-app-fiix-could-change-the-way-you-get-your-car-serviced', 'FIIX Could Change the Way You Get Your Car Serviced ', 'The Toronto app, described as “Uber for mechanics,” aims to bring top-rated mobile mechanics directly to your home to service your car. ', '', 'The Toronto app, described as “an Uber for mechanics,” aims to bring top-rated mobile mechanics directly to your home to service your car. ', '[FIIX](https://www.fiix.io/) is a platform for an industry that hasn’t seen a tech revolution yet. The Toronto app, described as “an Uber for mechanics,” aims to bring mechanics directly to your home to service your car. \r\n\r\nWhile getting a car serviced away from a service centre sounds like a complicated deal, the app promises that most common car works can be done easily by a mechanic anywhere with the right tools for the job.\r\n\r\nFiix’s founder also said that brining the mechanic right to the customer’s house actually makes it more cost effective for the customer as they do not have to pay for repairs that aren’t necessary but may be up-sold by garage sales and service managers.\r\n\r\nThe mechanics too benefit from the app as they don’t work on a commission-basis and hence have no incentive to sell repairs which cars don’t need. Cutting out the middle man, the service garage and its staff, helps the customer save a good amount of money. \r\n\r\nTransparency between mechanics and car owners is also something the app is hoping to increase. The website features repair details and a cost calculator so customers won’t have to worry about a mysterious repair that comes up after the mechanic has inspected the car. \r\n\r\nCustomers can request a general inspection service, where a mechanic will inspect the car to determine if it needs any repairs or servicing. If the car owners get the repairs made by the Fiix mechanic, then the inspection is at no cost.  \r\n\r\nThe platform now has 8 mechanics and will eventually expand nationally. The Fiix founding team got $25,000 during a Velocity Fund finals demo and $20,000 from Y Combinator business accelerator.', 0, 18, NULL, 0, 1, NULL, 'The Toronto app, described as “an Uber for mechanics,” aims to bring top-rated mobile mechanics directly to your home to service your car.', 'Staff', '', '2016-09-07 04:01:33', '2016-09-07 04:02:00'),
(202, 'Top 5 Ways to Keep Your Business Efficient During the Summer Slowdown', 'top-5-ways-to-keep-your-business-efficient-during-summer', 'Top Ways to Keep Your Business Efficient During the Summer', 'When it is summertime it can seem like many of your clients are not around and your inbox is almost empty except for some auto-replies. It can be frustrating if', '', 'When it is summertime it can seem like many of your clients are not around and your inbox is almost empty except for some auto-replies. It can be frustrating if you aren’t on a break yourself but everyone around you seems to be on one.', 'When it is summertime it can seem like many of your clients are not around and your inbox is almost empty except for some auto-replies. It can be frustrating if you aren’t on a break yourself but everyone around you seems to be on one. However you can make the best of the calmer season by actually getting ahead and making your business stronger.\r\n\r\n**Here are 5 ways to use your summer time to build your business:**\r\n\r\n### Pitch Prospective Clients\r\nRemember that your completion is probably in vacation mode, this is the ideal time to get ahead and make new business relationships. Don’t forget that your clients too could be on vacation but someone from their team may reply in their absence thus helping you build more contacts. \r\n\r\n### Reconnect With Your Network\r\nThere are probably some clients or co-workers you have been meaning to have a lunch meeting with, now is the time to make it happen. Make a list of meetings you want to set up and send out invitations. Your relationships with your business associates and clients could get a lot better this summer if you decide to take the initiative to make it.  \r\n\r\n### Meet With Your Team\r\nSpending more time with your team can make any business leader’s work a lot better. Use the lean summer months to connect with your employees and indulge in some team building activities. This is also the best time to plan the office fun trip you have always wanted to but never had the time for. \r\n\r\n### Do an Audit\r\nThis too can be difficult to do when you are terribly busy, use your summer to comb through your company’s expenses and decide on what changes can be implemented. Analyze your expenses and prioritise, you can also do some prep work for the months ahead.  \r\n\r\n### Make Time for Yourself\r\nWhile this is something you should do all the time anyway, it is not always possible. Use the summer to make some time for yourself and plan some fun activities or relaxing activities depending on what exactly you need. This can also be the best time to bring something new to your schedule, whertter it is a new exercise, an experience or just business related reading.  \r\nDon’t forget to enjoy the summer while using these slow months as an opportunity to bring more success to your business.', 0, 21, NULL, 0, 1, NULL, 'When it is summertime it can seem like many of your clients are not around and your inbox is almost empty except for some auto-replies. It can be frustrating if you aren’t on a break yourself but everyone around you seems to be on one. However you can make the best of the calmer season by actually getting ahead and making your business stronger.', 'Staff', '', '2016-09-08 03:35:50', '2016-09-08 03:36:11'),
(203, 'Hot housing market benefits Vancouver''s high-end furniture business', 'vancouver-high-end-furniture-business-housing-market-benefits', 'Hot Housing Good for Vancouver''s Furniture Business', 'Vancouver''s Hot housing market good for the high-end furniture business.', 'http://cdn.shopify.com/s/files/1/0163/6562/products/Mu-coffee-table_1024x1024.jpg?v=1443135916', 'As prices of homes increase the quality and price of the furniture in these homes too is rising if interior experts are to be believed. \r\nWhile prices of homes have been steadily rising, Vancouver’s benchmark furniture prices have increased 46 percent over the past two years.', 'Suquet Interiors, a business popular in Vancouver design circles, has been revived this summer. The timing is perfect. As Vancouver''s housing market is getting more heated than it already is, furniture sales grow stronger than ever. \r\n\r\nAs prices of homes increase the quality and price of the furniture in these homes too is rising if interior experts are to be believed. \r\nWhile prices of homes have been steadily rising, Vancouver’s benchmark furniture prices have increased 46 percent over the past two years.\r\n \r\n “I guess when you suddenly find yourself living in a million-dollar home, that faded 10-year-old couch just seems out of place,” Guatieri wrote in BMO’s AM Charts June report.\r\n\r\nThe increase of higher end furniture sales is something that interior experts have anticipated in the wake of higher prices for homes and more foreign investment coming in. \r\n\r\nThe market is just right for Suquet to swoop away the buyers as they are focused on the higher end market and it not only the people who are buying new homes but renovating to upgrade who are looking for quality furniture for their upgraded home.  \r\n\r\n“A lot of bigger homes are being built. If you’re going to spend upwards of $6- to $16-million on a home, you want quality furniture.” A company representative recently said. \r\n\r\n<p style="font-weight: bold;text-align: center;"><a href="http://www.kqzyfj.com/10107uoxuowBKDFDDDEBDCIJFCGFBDGIKKIEFGICCC" target="_blank" onmouseover="window.status=''https://orders.freedomvoice.com/secure-order?utm_term=800-numbers'';return true;" onmouseout="window.status='' '';return true;">Get an 800 number</a> and try it FREE for 30 days!<img src="http://www.ftjcfx.com/ef103ltxlrpAJCECCCDACBHIEBFEACFHJJHDEFHBBB" width="1" height="1" border="0"/></p>\r\n\r\nWith much of retail turning online for profits the furniture business is not one that can reap bounties online as customers would prefer to see their higher end furniture pieces in person before making a decision. Also the heavy nature of inventory makes delivery and returns much more difficult than an average retail order. The company said that competition in the furniture market is expected to increase over the next five years. \r\n\r\nSuquet has some artisanal pieces that are very trendy now, however they cater to various types of styles of interior. “Anybody in furniture retail needs to be prepared for change,” a company representative said adding that diversification was very important. \r\n\r\nAs more foreign investments come into our real estate markets, other sectors like furniture and interiors businesses are benefiting from the influx of cash into the sectors. Bigger homes being sold are likely to need more furniture, which is usually not of the cheaper variety but the higher end brands available. So while housing prices sky rocket we can probably appreciate this small silver lining.', 0, 16, 5, 0, 1, NULL, 'As prices of homes increase the quality and price of the furniture in these homes too is rising if interior experts are to be believed. \r\nWhile prices of homes have been steadily rising, Vancouver’s benchmark furniture prices have increased 46 percent over the past two years.', 'Staff', '', '2016-09-15 05:30:45', '2016-10-09 00:07:48'),
(204, 'Real Estate Bidding Wars in Toronto Are Now Real, Say Buyers', 'real-estate-bidding-wars-milton-toronto-now-real-say-buyers', 'Real Estate Bidding Wars in Milton, Toronto Are Now Real', 'The Milton, Toronto real estate market has seen spikes, but these days buyers are ready to pay substantial amounts of money above the asking price.', 'http://vertica.ca/files/styles/property_gallery/public/property/amenities/glen-eden-street.jpg', 'The real estate market has seen various spikes in the past year but these days buyers are ready to pay substantial amounts of money above the asking price ', 'The real estate market has seen various spikes in the past year but these days buyers are ready to pay substantial amounts of money above the asking price and settle for deals that come with almost no conditions, according to buyers. \r\n\r\nWhile good listings are facing intense competition, desperate buyers are now resorting to paying much over the asking price so ensure they are able to winner the round of bidding and land the deal.\r\n\r\nRemember that these are not isolated cases, such bidding wars are now apparently the norm in Toronto’s housing market, but these wars are now extending to the suburbs which are probably an hour’s drive from the city and into smaller cities like [Newmarket](/article/newmarket-real-estate-information) and [Barrie](/article/barrie-real-estate-information).  The hot housing market is making it very difficult for an average buyer to consider buying a new house even in suburbs when the housing battles are now much more intense. \r\n\r\nVolumes of homes sold in the suburbs were actually much higher than the resales made in the city itself, which makes the bidding wars even more difficult to entertain. Prices for detached houses have increased 15 percent from a year earlier, the [Toronto Real Estate Board](/tag/treb) said. \r\n\r\n**See also: [TREB Must Provide Home Sales Data Online: Competition Tribunal](/article/treb-must-provide-home-sales-data-online)**\r\n\r\nNorthwest of the city, In Milton, condo and house prices increased by a whopping 42 percent this year. This aggressive increase has been attributed to the bidding wars that have been prevalent. \r\n\r\nEstate agents say they began noticing a change last fall when houses in Milton that came up for sale started to become involved in bidding wars. Many estate agents were caught off-guard they claim. From seeing almost no houses in the suburbs going over asking price they now are seeing offers on listings that go well over the asking price. \r\n\r\nBuyers prefer the suburban houses due to low interest rates, easy employment access etc. The Toronto suburbs also are seeing growth in jobs and higher rates of immigration. Another reason for the unprecedented increase in the housing market prices has been said to be foreign investors who are now looking to invest in not just city areas but in many suburbs as well. They are ready to pay well over the asking price and usually have no problem with buying houses with the existing further in them. \r\n\r\nChinese buyers pay the top dollar for properties some estate agents say, “They consider our housing market as a safe place to put their investments in,”\r\nThe houses in the suburbs are now evolving; new constructed homes are aimed at wealthier buyers and are increasing the average price of suburban homes. Million dollar homes are now becoming the norm, an estate agent says. \r\n\r\nSome real estate agents also mention that while demand is increasing significantly, supply is not increasing proportionally but in-fact is actually going down.  This has led to many local buyers being pushed out the suburban locales they would have preferred into regions further away. Most real estate agents feel that the trend is not looking like it will change anytime soon and that prices are expected to stay high.', 0, 16, NULL, 0, 1, NULL, 'The real estate market has seen various spikes in the past year but these days buyers are ready to pay substantial amounts of money above the asking price', 'Staff', '', '2016-09-16 03:26:27', '2016-10-09 00:27:31'),
(205, 'Tips When Selling to Asian Real Estate Buyers', 'tips-when-selling-to-asian-real-estate-buyers', 'Tips When Selling to Asian Real Estate Buyers', 'The volatility in the Chinese economy along with the benefits of the low loonie makes Canada an attractive destination for investors.', 'http://yorkvillecondoblog.co/wp-content/uploads/2013/06/China-Canada-Flags-Victoria-Boscariol-Chestnut-Park-Real-Estate.jpg', 'Remember that Asia is a huge market and respecting the intricacies of business relationships with foreign clients can be difficult, but do not let it hinder you. ', 'As more Asians look for real estate investments in Canada it has become important to appeal to their property requirements while attracting a good deal. \r\n\r\nThe volatility in the Chinese economy and stock market along with the benefits of the low loonie makes Canada an attractive place for Chinese buyers as they see the real estate market here as a stable investment. \r\n\r\nFurther, the Chinese aren’t the only Asians interested in [buying property in Canada](/category/real-estate/) as many investors from Singapore, Taiwan and Hong Kong are heading here to make real estate investments. \r\n\r\nHigh returns from property investments and a strong economy is making Canada a good bet for investments, As [more Asians are considering Canada a safe investment](/article/5-percent-of-all-vancouver-homes-sold-are-bought-by-foreigners) in their uncertain economic times, there are also other factors leading to these investments that are not purely financial. \r\n\r\nPersonal property laws are also a reason for the continued real estate interest from Asians apart from the strong cultural diversity.\r\n\r\nWhile it may seem like there are many interested buyers, getting a good deal on a property is a lot easier if you know how to appeal to these buyers. While Asians are different from Canadians in many ways there can be good ways to make the whole process a lot easier for both the buyers and the seller.\r\n\r\n<p style="font-weight: bold;text-align: center;"><a href="http://www.kqzyfj.com/10107uoxuowBKDFDDDEBDCIJFCGFBDGIKKIEFGICCC" target="_blank" onmouseover="window.status=''https://orders.freedomvoice.com/secure-order?utm_term=800-numbers'';return true;" onmouseout="window.status='' '';return true;">Get an 800 number</a> and try it FREE for 30 days!<img src="http://www.ftjcfx.com/ef103ltxlrpAJCECCCDACBHIEBFEACFHJJHDEFHBBB" width="1" height="1" border="0" data-pagespeed-url-hash="4241178305" onload="pagespeed.CriticalImages.checkImageForCriticality(this);"/></p>\r\n\r\nEspecially with more traditional customers, an important thing to remember is the importance of superstitious and omens. This is especially true when buying property since they give importance to feng shui, which governs spatial arrangement and orientation in relation to the flow of energy in buildings.\r\n\r\nAsian buyers will usually check the basic feng shui of a house themselves or may get it checked by an expert. Your personal views about the concept are immaterial as you should be sensitive about the buyer’s preferences. Buyers pay attention to the direction the main door of the house faces and the positioning of the staircase, the address number is also an important factor in their property selection as some numbers are considered luckier than others. Hiring a feng shui expert to certify the house could mean more bids on the house. \r\n\r\nEven a simple act of handing over your business card to an Asian buyer can be significant. Use both your hands to hand over the card and similarly receive a card handed to your with both your hands. Asians respect and value their traditions, and while they do understand that it is not possible for others to know everything, it can make a big a big difference in the business relationship if you make an effort to respect their culture. \r\n\r\n**See also: [Vancouver''s High-End Furniture Business Benefits From Real Estate Boom](/article/vancouver-high-end-furniture-business-housing-market-benefits)**\r\n\r\nThis is also especially important when it comes to eating out and choosing food. Food is an important part of doing business in Asia. While eating out at a restaurant you pick is totally acceptable don’t hesitate to ask for their preference of cuisine. Also, don’t make comments about how certain dishes are very unusual, they probably grew up eating it and could easily get offended.  \r\n\r\nWhile language is now no longer a huge issue, it can be a great advantage to have someone who can speak the language of the buyer as some buyers may have issues communicating in English.\r\n \r\nRemember that Asia is a huge market and respecting the intricacies of business relationships with foreign clients can be difficult, but do not let it hinder you.', 0, 16, 21, 0, 1, NULL, 'The volatility in the Chinese economy and stock market along with the benefits of the low loonie makes Canada an attractive place for Chinese buyers as they see the real estate market here as a stable investment.', 'Staff', '', '2016-09-18 16:44:20', '2016-10-09 00:23:19'),
(206, 'Title Company Fraud and How to Spot Other Real Estate Scams', 'how-to-spot-a-real-estate-scam', 'Title Company Fraud and Other Real Estate Scams', 'How to spot the most common real estate frauds, including title company fraud, foreclosure and home-equity fraud, property investment seminars and others.', 'http://www.newyorkrealestatelawyersblog.com/wp-content/uploads/sites/164/2016/03/fraud.jpg', 'From tittle fraud to fake investment seminars and home Improvement scams there are a number of things to watch out for. Here are some of the most common ones.', 'Scams and fraud investments exists just about everywhere these days, from the emails which claim to be from a long lost relative of a prince to the more larger scale wall street investment scams. In the world of real estate there are scams that every buyer needs to be aware about. Protecting yourself from these scams can actually require more vigilance that you would think. \r\nHere are 5 real estate scams and how to spot them. \r\n\r\n### Title Company Fraud	\r\nThis is possibly the fraud with the worst consequences. The fraud starts with identity theft, the scammer poses as the real property owner and using forged documents transfers the property to his own name and even gets a mortgage on the house. After he secures a mortgage the scammer flees with the cash leaving the real owner pay for future payments. These types of scammers tend to prefer homes that don’t have existing mortgages and people who are less likely to know about identity theft. Home owners who rent out their homes or have no mortgage on it are more likely to become targets of this fraud. The best way to be protected from this scam is to take insurance that provides coverage against title fraud though title insurance.\r\n\r\nSpotting this fraud can be difficult but protection of personal data is very important in preventing such scams. Home owners should take extra precaution while protecting their documents and identity related paperwork and possibly look into title insurance.\r\n\r\nRemember that identity theft is not something that can only be committed by strangers. There have been instances where spouses have mortgaged property without telling their spouse. It could also be a lawyer or notary who is committing the crime of absconding with the funds. \r\n\r\n### Foreclosure and home-equity fraud\r\nThis type of real estate fraud usually takes advantage of a property owner who is short on mortgage, there are two common ways scammers exploit a home owner’s need for cash. In a foreclosure fraud, the owner of the property is approached by a scammer who offers a loan to cover the mortgage; this is the real-estate version of the email-scam. Scammer claim to charge an initial fee for processing the loan and later make the owners sign an agreement to transfer the property title. The scammer then remortgages the house and makes away with the money, the property owner is still left with his original mortgage but now he has no house. This is one of the most popular types of mortgage fraud.\r\n\r\n### Online property rental and sales scams \r\nWhere most online property advertisements are real, there are scammers there too. They advertise property at low rates in online sites such as Craigslist and then demand the payment for the rental either online or at another place. The scam is that the property does not belong to them in reality; they are simply impersonating the owner and claiming to rent out the house. When the renters arrive at the property they realise they were being duped all along.  The best to spot a scam is to remember that if something looks too good to be true it probably is. Another tip is to rely on the more sought after real estate rental websites. \r\n\r\n### Property investment seminars and courses\r\nAttending seminars and courses on property investment can be a great way to learn more, but here too you could get scammed. While these are not as bad as the other scams we have talked about, these scams could make you spend substantial amounts of money without providing quality return on your investment. \r\n\r\nWhile there are many good real estate experts who could have good quality seminars it is better to err on the side of caution while picking a seminar to attend especially if you are paying a steep charge. Try to stay away from seminars that suggest you make high risk investments. \r\n\r\n**[How to Spot 7 Common Investment Scams](/article/7-investment-scams-to-stay-away-from)**\r\n\r\n### Home Improvement scams\r\nThese are lower-end scams but bad nonetheless. These scammers claim they can work for cheap rates because they have material leftover from a previous job. An easy way to spot a home improvement scams is the high pressure sales tactics they use. \r\n\r\nThe best way to stay away from being scammed is to not pay in cash for home repairs upfront and to always hire someone who has a recommendation from a friend or neighbour.', 0, 16, NULL, 0, 1, NULL, 'From tittle fraud to fake investment seminars and home Improvement scams there are a number of things to watch out for. Here are some of the most common ones.', 'Staff', '', '2016-09-18 16:54:08', '2016-09-30 04:24:39'),
(207, 'Should Trade Barriers Between Canada and Japan Be Removed?', 'free-trade-between-canada-and-japan-coming', 'Free Trade Between Canada and Japan?', 'There are negotiations that are now underway that could bring about changes to trade and a free trade agreement is anticipated too.', '', 'Japan and Canada, despite having a long history of trade together remain distinct in many ways, however there is a growing anticipation in the business community that the two countries will become closer economically in the future.', 'Japan and Canada, despite having a long history of trade together remain distinct in many ways. Both countries tend to give larger markets like the U.S. and China more business attention however there is a growing anticipation in the business community that the two countries will become closer economically in the future. \r\n\r\nAs more protectionism is expected in trade policy in the U.S. and with the Brexit vote making the country move further away from integrating with other players in the global economy, Canada is seen as an attractive option. \r\n\r\nU.S. restrained trade policies could also make other Asian countries head over to Canada. Japan and Canada have had an uncomplicated business relationship with Canadian companies exporting raw materials to Japan and Japan exporting manufacturing goods to Canada.  \r\n\r\nCanada exported around $9.6 billion worth of goods to Japan in 2015, the relationship between Japan and Canada could be a lot more natural in the years to come. \r\n\r\nThe sheer size of the Japanese market makes it an attractive, experts say. The country could also be a gateway to larger markets. All of this is possible if trade barriers between the two countries are removed. \r\n \r\nThe trading methodology could change, there are negotiations that are now underway that could bring about these changes. A free trade agreement is anticipated too. There are currently other efforts being taken to bring about changes in the business economy linking both countries. \r\n\r\nCanada has always been ready to change the traditional relationship it has with Japan, some experts feel. Both countries are looking forward to finding new ways to make significant investments in the corporate world. \r\n\r\nThere are many opportunities for Canada and Japan to forge better business relationships. One such is using Canada’s wealth of experience in public-private partnerships for knowledge transfer.  \r\n\r\nOne of the main reasons new partnerships between the two countries is important is the importance given to free trade in both nations. Public-private partnership deals are common in various sectors including transportation and infrastructure \r\n\r\nAnother sector relevant to the modern society is digital economy which is increasingly becoming more important.  This could be especially important if the Trans-Pacific Partnership which would govern consumers in 12 countries is signed. \r\n\r\nWhile Japan and Canada have had a good business relationship over the years, maybe this time it is time to step it up at notch which includes the digital economy where the real change can happen?', 0, 7, NULL, 0, 1, NULL, 'Japan and Canada, despite having a long history of trade together remain distinct in many ways, however there is a growing anticipation in the business community that the two countries will become closer economically in the future.', 'Staff', '', '2016-09-20 03:54:03', '2016-09-20 03:54:33'),
(208, 'As Food Subscription Boxes Fade Away, Carnivore Club Stays Strong.', 'as-food-subscription-boxes-fade-away-carnivore-club-stays-strong', 'Carnivore Club Grows As Food Subscription Boxes Fade', 'Subscription-based e-commerce company Carnivore Club is proving to be much more than just a one trick pony.', '', 'Subscription-based e-commerce company Carnivore Club, that that delivers cured meat to the homes of members, was first launched subscription boxes were the things to be buying.', 'Subscription-based e-commerce company Carnivore Club is proving to be much more than just a one trick pony. When the service, that delivers cured meat to the homes of members, was first launched subscription boxes were the things to be buying, however over time the subscription box trend started fading away.\r\n\r\nWhat remains surprising is, when the subscription box trend was no longer the latest thing to try, this particular service still remained relevant to its loyal customers. While other companies in the same arena where facing a hard time with buyers not returning to renew subscriptions, Carnivore Club was raking in the subscribers. \r\n\r\n> ### “Our U.S. revenue has been exceeding Canadian revenue, which was the goal. We knew there was no reason our Canadian revenue should be higher than U.S. revenue.”\r\n\r\nThe company, which appeared on Dragon’s Den, is soon planning to launch in Australia and has seen exponential growth in its U.S. revenue.\r\nCarnivore Club, which appeared in season 9 of Dragon’s Den, impressed the dragons, who liked its recurring revenue model, and went on to sign a royalty deal with David Chilton.\r\n\r\n“Our U.S. revenue has been exceeding Canadian revenue, which was the goal. We knew there was no reason our Canadian revenue should be higher than U.S. revenue.” A co-founder of the company recently told a major news organization. \r\n\r\nCarnivore Club also plans to expand its line of products and is set to launch a jerky club and an exotic meat club apart from rebranding its existing range. \r\n\r\nThe company, which has an increased number of members every month, doubled its revenue in its first year. Memberships are usually either fixed term gift subscriptions, monthly or bimonthly subscriptions. \r\n\r\nThe company is also looking to start a club for the European Union since its European members are now predominantly in Britain. It looks to source suppliers from other European countries too. \r\n\r\nIn the U.S. and Canada it employs a model where orders are fulfilled by local artisans. This direct delivery method seems to have helped the company speed up its evolution. As the company is scaling up its processes it is using a specially designed model where direct delivery and fulfillment partners are used. \r\n\r\nThe company is now looking at creating a rebranded version of itself with a new website right in time for the holidays, which is the best time for products aimed at being gifts.', 0, 18, NULL, 0, 1, NULL, 'Subscription-based e-commerce company Carnivore Club is proving to be much more than just a one trick pony. When the service, that delivers cured meat to the homes of members, was first launched subscription boxes were the things to be buying, however over time the subscription box trend started fading away.', 'Staff', '', '2016-09-29 01:35:24', '2016-09-29 01:37:30'),
(209, 'Quebec Hydroelectric Firm Under Scanner for Bad Environmental Standards in Albania', 'quebec-hydroelectric-firm-under-scanner-for-bad-environmental-standards-in-albania', 'Quebec Hydroelectric Project Under Scrutiny in Albania ', 'A team of Canadian engineers are building hydroelectric dams in Albania in what is seen as a controversial move.', '', 'Now, a team of Canadian engineers are building hydroelectric dams in Albania in what is seen as a controversial move as the dam, built across the Balkans, is said to have bad environmental standards with critics claiming it could destroy the rivers in the project. ', 'Since Hydro-Québec was nationalized in the 1960s, Quebec has had a good reputation in the international hydroelectric engineering sector. The largest hydroelectric systems in the world, the James Bay Project, further helped get the expertise noticed. \r\n\r\nNow, a team of Canadian engineers are building hydroelectric dams in Albania in what is seen as a controversial move as the dam, built across the Balkans, is said to have bad environmental standards with critics claiming it could destroy the rivers in the project. \r\n\r\nCritics have also called the project a ‘dam tsunami’, referring to seismic waves which could cause huge harm and also claim the project is covered in corruption.\r\n\r\nMontreal based company Hydro Investment recently completed a dam in Albania, it said its project is environmentally strong and showcases Canada’s expertise in hydroelectric installations.\r\n\r\nSoutheastern Europe uses less than half of its hydropower potential according to experts. Albania is no exception, the country which is now open to foreign investment thanks to free-market reforms in infrastructure needs the electricity generated by the hydroelectric installations. \r\n\r\nAlbania’s aging hydroelectric power plants generate a huge part of the energy the country needs while it has to import about a third of energy it uses. \r\nThere are about 611 future projects in the Balkan region that is expected to add a total capacity of about 18 gigawatts, Christiane Zarfl, a professor at the Leibniz-Institute of Freshwater Ecology and Inland Fisheries in Berlin recently said. \r\n\r\nOf these around four dams of at least one megawatt are already under construction, this, without including smaller projects which are being planned or already under construction. \r\n\r\nHydropower is the preferred choice for the Balkan region not only as it is a flexible and renewable energy source but since the potential of rivers still remains high. There are several rivers that could be used to build more dams, Zarfl added. \r\n\r\nSources have that the government of Albania has given concession for at least 435 hydropower projects. While Hydropower is seen as a safe renewable source, critics and environmental activists claim the harmful effects and environmental impact is important to look into. Diverting rivers can block species migrations and disrupt ecosystems, they said.  \r\n\r\nThe destruction of a pristine habitat could lead to many issues the ecosystem would not suffer but even other ecosystem services such as drinking water supply to humans could be affected. \r\n\r\nDams are destroying the few remaining pristine rivers in Europe and the unique ecosystem that surround it. Given the huge number of dams planned, some species could go extinct, the critics point out. \r\n\r\nHowever it remains important to note that none of these companies are flouting rules. Even the critics understand that the companies cannot be lawfully approached and the only course of action they have towards protecting the eco system is a moral obligation. \r\n\r\nWhile Albania’s need for reliable electricity is understandable it should use a more diversified method to deal to bring the best of power generating techniques to the forefront including using more solar and wind energy in addition to building dams to use hydro power.', 0, 15, 0, 0, 1, NULL, 'Now, a team of Canadian engineers are building hydroelectric dams in Albania in what is seen as a controversial move as the dam, built across the Balkans, is said to have bad environmental standards with critics claiming it could destroy the rivers in the project.', 'Staff', '', '2016-09-29 01:42:59', '2016-09-29 01:42:59'),
(210, 'Vancouver''s Foreign Buyer Tax Leads to Trump Tower Buyers Not Closing Sales', 'vancouver-foreign-buyer-tax-leads-trump-tower-buyers-not-closing-deals', 'Vancouver''s Foreign Buyer Tax Means Trump Tower Issues', 'The Trump International Hotel and Tower in Vancouver set a record price when it was sold out, however the 15 percent foreign buyer tax is leading to problems.', 'http://vuosiamaailmalla.fi/blog/wp-content/uploads/2014/trump_tower35.jpg', 'The Trump International Hotel and Tower in Vancouver set a record price when it was sold out, however it now looks like the 15 percent foreign buyer tax being implemented is making presale buyers uncomfortable. ', 'Holborn Group CEO and Developer Joo Kim Tiahsaid the tax has affected offshore presale buyers who have now decided they don’t want to close the deal in the wake of the 15 percent tax levy. The group said it has sold all the luxuary condos in the tower at an average $1,615 per square foot, which sets a new record for a condo in Canada.\r\n\r\nLuxuary penthouses in the tower are expected to priced starting are $20 million when they are available next year. \r\n\r\nThe developers have admitted that a small percentage of buyers are now saying they can’t close the deal and that they are helping them get financing to help finalize the sale. \r\n\r\nAnother trend some foreign buyers are practicing is to assign their properties to a Canadian relative, this is becoming an industry practice to close the deals at the price initially agreed upon, some experts say. Assigning to relatives is a common phenomenon in presales; however it can only be assigned at the agreed-upon price so buyers don’t flip the property. \r\n\r\nAbout 10 percent of the units at Trump Tower were purchased by buyers who had foreign passports, Developer Joo Kim Tiahsaid said. \r\n\r\nThe new tax applies to purchases that were in process, this was something experts seem to agree was uncalled for as the stability of deals made was hurt by it. Buyers who entered into contracts a couple of years ago now have to pay 15 percent more.  \r\n\r\nThe property transfer gets paid when a buyer registers ownership with the land titles office, since presales are made years in advance it doesn’t get paid until residents take occupancy.  This is especially bad for developers whose buildings are nearing completion as presale buyers could rather lose their deposit than raise an additional 15 percent to close the deal. \r\n\r\n**See also: [Chinese Nationals Make up Most of 5% of Vancouver Homes Sold to Non-Canadians](/article/5-percent-of-all-vancouver-homes-sold-are-bought-by-foreigners)**\r\n\r\nThis new tax has also changed developers minds on assignments, developers who were not fully happy about assignments earlier now realise it is their interest.  \r\n\r\nAssignments don’t really work unless it is with a trusted relative or close friend; the buyer is literally selling their rights to the property. It may be transferred back later but since all transactions are covered by the revenue agency it can be difficult to make large payments to your relative without dealing with issues. \r\n\r\nSome experts feel that the time is right for Canadian buyers to close deals as some foreign buyers are not eager to buy.  While volume of real estate sales is expected to decrease in the next few months, most experts agree that the tax is not going to have a lasting impact on the real estate economy.\r\nThe 15 percent foreign buyer tax is not the first issue the tower is facing it has previously been in the news for new ownership and lawsuits by investors.', 0, 16, 8, 0, 1, NULL, 'The Trump International Hotel and Tower in Vancouver set a record price when it was sold out, however it now looks like the 15 percent foreign buyer tax being implemented is making presale buyers uncomfortable.', 'Staff', '', '2016-10-02 17:42:56', '2016-10-02 17:48:25'),
(211, 'How to Have a Productive Day When You Aren''t Feeling Great', 'how-to-have-a-productive-day-when-you-arent-feeling-great', 'How to Have a Productive Day When You Aren''t Feeling Great', 'Even the most motivated people can have such a day sometimes, here''s some tips on how to overcome it. ', '', 'There are some days when you can’t get out of bed simply because you feel terribly lethargic and don’t want to work. Even the most motivated people can have such a day sometimes. So how does one deal with it? ', 'There are some days when you can’t get out of bed simply because you feel terribly lethargic and don’t want to work. When you do manage to get dressed at head to work you realize you are having a terribly unproductive day. Even the most motivated people can have such a day sometimes. So how does one deal with it? \r\n\r\nImproving your time management is the best way to enjoy a productive day even when your spirit is not as high as it should be. Don’t aim to finish a ton of work, but aim to complete a couple of important tasks that are important and bring your closer to your goals. \r\n\r\nOn such days remind yourself that it is the quality of work that is important not the quantity, here are some ways to turn a bad day into a productive one\r\nIdentify the 3 most important tasks of the day. \r\n\r\nWhile this is relevant for any ordinary day at work, it is especially necessary when you know you are having an unproductive day. Getting the most important tasks finished first is the best way to get things done productively. It is easy to get distracted and lose focus and the best way to stay focused is to only focus on the most important tasks at hand. Choose the important asks based on the action they bring towards your goal. \r\n\r\n### Rank them\r\nOnce you have identified the tasks you intend to complete, make them the main focus of your day. Write down the tasks and tick them off when you finish them. Number them in order of urgency and importance, Number 1 should be the most important one and 3 the least important among the three. \r\n\r\n### Next set of three important tasks \r\nOnce you have identified the first set of three most important tasks, move on to identifying the next of three most important tasks of the day in the same manner. Try to work in sets of three and think of your tasks as sets. Like the reps at the gym, soon you will plan all your tasks in a similar way. \r\n\r\n### Schedule your tasks \r\nScheduling your three most important tasks ahead of time is a great way to ensure you get it done on time. You have already planned it there is nothing else to do but get it done right? \r\n\r\n### Tackle the most important task first \r\nGetting the most important task finished first is the best way to make your day already seem like a productive one. The impact from completing your most important task will help you in your other tasks as you already feel like you have accomplished something for the day. \r\n\r\n### Set a timer \r\nChoose a block of time you would like to work for, it could be 30 minutes to 45 minutes. When your alarm rings you should stop working, but not until it does. \r\n\r\nUsing this approach will help you stay clear of all distractions and you will be less tempted to quickly check your Facebook page. Try to put your phone a little away when you are working, turn the notifications off on text messages but have your ringer on for phone calls. \r\n\r\n**See also: [5 Ways to Stop Procrastination in Its Tracks](/article/top-15-ways-to-stop-procrastination-in-its-tracks)**\r\n\r\n### Take a break \r\nTaking a quick break before you start another task is the best way to go into it with a fresh mind. But remember that your break shouldn’t run longer than the task itself. You could take a quick walk, clean out your desk or do any other office related chores you may have or if you really must then use this time to check your Facebook. \r\n\r\n### Use your momentum to get further \r\nOnce you complete an important task, you will feel a lot more positive than earlier, use this momentum to give you a boost to do well on the other tasks.', 0, 21, NULL, 0, 1, NULL, 'There are some days when you can’t get out of bed simply because you feel terribly lethargic and don’t want to work. When you do manage to get dressed at head to work you realize you are having a terribly unproductive day. Even the most motivated people can have such a day sometimes. So how does one deal with it?', 'Staff', '', '2016-10-03 02:13:28', '2016-10-08 04:09:58'),
(212, 'Top 8 Customer Service Tips for Closing on National Holidays', '8-customer-service-tips-closing-national-holidays', '8 Tips For Customer Service When Going on Holiday', 'Every good entrepreneur finds it difficult to take time off, however it important to take some vacation time or time off work in general to reduce your stress.', 'http://fieldskill.co/wp-content/uploads/2015/06/business-on-vacation.jpg', 'Every good entrepreneur finds it difficult to take time off, however it important to take some vacation time or time off work in general to reduce your stress levels', 'Every good entrepreneur finds it difficult to take time off, however it important to take some vacation time or time off work in general to reduce your stress levels and constant exposure to high pressure situations which can have an impact on your productivity. \r\n\r\nTaking a weekend off or enjoying a national holiday can make a great difference in your productivity levels and general business attitude. Being well rested will help you not only stay more calm and relaxed but also be more empathic towards others which is very essential in good customer service. \r\n\r\nHere are some tips to make customer service better on national holidays:\r\n\r\n1. **Don’t send out marketing emails on holidays or Fridays.** Not only will people not open their email they will most probably ignore it if they do. Save it for the next week. \r\n\r\n1. **Let your customers know that you are closed.** Have it on your voice mail, social media accounts, website or even an email if someone mails you directly. Don’t spam them though. \r\n\r\n1. **Don’t stay open if you know you need a vacation.** Customers will understand that you are closed. Focus on your relationships with your family and friends instead. \r\n\r\n1. **Use social media to get festive.** Show people you are excited for the holidays. Create festive images that include your company’s name and logo to make it more visually appealing to customers.\r\n\r\n**See also: [Have a Productive Day When You Aren''t Feeling Great](/article/how-to-have-a-productive-day-when-you-arent-feeling-great)**\r\n\r\n1. **Don’t post any pictures that you would not show a customer who walks into your workplace.** That great picture of you at the beach, keep it on your personal Facebook page.  \r\n\r\n1. **You love your customers, but remember that there are other people in your life.** Don’t spend your vacation checking the company Facebook page. \r\n\r\n1. **Don’t bring any work with you on vacation.** This should be a given, but unfortunately it’s often not. Also, don’t spend more time on the phone than you really need to.\r\n\r\n1. **Enjoy the holidays doing something fun.** Whether it is binge watching Shark Tank or going for a long walk, make sure it is something you truly enjoy. \r\n\r\nEnjoy the holidays and come back with a rejuvenated body and soul! ', 0, 21, NULL, 0, 1, NULL, 'Every good entrepreneur finds it difficult to take time off, however it important to take some vacation time or time off work in general to reduce your stress levels', 'Staff', '', '2016-10-06 04:25:45', '2016-10-06 04:32:49');
