(213, 'Top 15 Ways to Stop Procrastination in Its Tracks', 'top-15-ways-to-stop-procrastination-in-its-tracks', 'Stop Procrastination in Its Tracks With These 15 Tips', 'Postponing tasks is an issue that most knowledge workers face, when your work is not laid out for you, here are 15 tips to stop procrastination in its tracks.', '', 'Procrastination is easy, but it is also something that makes you feel terrible later. Postponing tasks is an issue that most knowledge workers face, when your work is not laid out for you, it can be very easy to procrastinate. Here are 15 tips to stop procrastination in its tracks.', 'Procrastination is easy, but it is also something that makes you feel terrible later. Postponing tasks is an issue that most knowledge workers face, when your work is not laid out for you, it can be very easy to procrastinate. \r\n\r\nIn most workplaces these days, employees identify and design their own schedule this makes it much more efficient to work better, however on a bad day it could also mean you are procrastinating for no good reason at all. Procrastination is basically avoiding doing a task which you need to get done, and doing less urgent things instead.  \r\n\r\nWhile procrastination can be a deep rooted problem in our modern society, there are many way we can personally overcome it to make our lives easier and reach our goals faster.\r\n\r\n### Here are 15 tips to stop procrastination and make your life a lot better:\r\n\r\n1. **Denial isn’t just a river in Egypt.** Acknowledging your Procrastination is the first step to eliminating it. Don’t be embarrassed, you aren’t the only one doing it. In fact it is a widely known fact that only intelligent people procrastinate. But once you acknowledge it you can then move on to acting on it.\r\n\r\n2. **Once you have acknowledged your tendency to procrastinate it is now time to determine why you are doing it.** Getting to the source of the problem is the best way to analyse it. Are you bored? Are the tasks not challenging enough? Learning more about your reason for postponing could be very important.\r\n\r\n3. **Understand that you cannot do everything at once.** You must prioritize your tasks and work on the most important ones first. Remember that completing one really important task is much more effective than spending a lot on time on unimportant tasks. Focus on the quality of work rather than trying to get more tasks done in a short time. Ask yourself if you are getting the intended results from your work.  \r\n\r\n4. **Asking others for help is often the best way to get things done.** If you are overwhelmed with the amount of work you have to do, don’t hesitate to ask someone for help. Remember that you have to start somewhere; you just have to decide where. \r\n\r\n5. **Visualise the benefits you would gain from completing your task well.** Understanding the benefits of completing your task can be a good motivator to get you getting started on a project.\r\n\r\n6. **Revisit your goals often to understand where you have reached.** Not only will your goals inspire you but you are less likely to want to procrastinate when you are thinking about your goals and the course of action to get there.\r\n\r\n7. **Break down your work into smaller tasks to accomplish.** Work towards completing those tasks within the time you have allocated for them. Be realistic while allocating time. Cutting down tasks into smaller sets also makes it easier for you to track progress \r\n\r\n**See also: [How to Have a Productive Day When You Aren''t Feeling Great](/article/how-to-have-a-productive-day-when-you-arent-feeling-great)**\r\n\r\n8. **Eliminated all distractions around you.** You know better than anyone the things that make you unproductive, keep them away from your workplace and place your phone upside down. \r\n\r\n9. **When you want to enjoy the things that you get distracted from work for, schedule them.** Making sure you have time allocated to these distractions ensures that the time you spend working is not wasted but you have something to look forward to.\r\n\r\n10. **Understand that perfection is not a necessity.** Sometimes it can pay to be imperfect. \r\n\r\n11. **Choose a single task and stick to it till you finish.** While multitasking is often associated with being more productive it is not recommended to those who are more prone to procrastination than others.\r\n\r\n12. **Changing your work environment can also be a great way to stop procrastination.** If you are working in bed then it is probably time to move to a desk. \r\n\r\n13. **The two minute task challenge** – if a task only takes two minutes to complete, do it right away. \r\n\r\n14. **Use bad experiences and unpleasant consequences to motivate yourself.** Tell yourself you can’t go to the movies this week if you don’t finish this task. Challenge yourself by coming up with innovative motivators every single time. \r\n\r\n15. **Instill a sense of urgency in you.** Use the Pomodoro technique with which when you work for 25 minutes without interruption, you then take a 5 minute break and then focus for another 25 minutes.\r\n\r\nUsing these tips will help you make your day a lot more productive and hopefully you will be motivated to use these tips in the long run. Next time you find yourself procrastinating, come back to this page.', 0, 21, NULL, 0, 1, NULL, 'Procrastination is easy, but it is also something that makes you feel terrible later. Postponing tasks is an issue that most knowledge workers face, when your work is not laid out for you, it can be very easy to procrastinate. Here are 15 tips to stop procrastination in its tracks.', 'Staff', '', '2016-10-08 04:00:47', '2016-10-08 04:08:09'),
(214, 'ATVTrailers Online Store for ATV and Quad-Trailers in Canada', 'atvtrailers-online-store-for-atv-and-quad-trailers-in-canada', 'ATVTrailers : ATV and Quad-Trailers in Canada', 'Canada is big and so are ATV trailers which means shipping from USA is expensive and time-consuming.', '', 'Canada is big and so are ATV trailers which means shipping from USA is expensive and time-consuming. They keep stock in Canada and thereby fill orders to Canadians quickly and at great prices. ', '[ATVTrailers.ca](http://ATVTrailers.ca) is an online business with one goal in mind: to bring the toughest ATV and quad trailers to Canada at affordable prices. This isn''t as easy as it sounds: Canada is big and so are ATV trailers which means shipping from USA is expensive and time-consuming. They keep stock in Canada and thereby provide orders to Canadians quickly and at great prices. \r\n\r\nTheir website is updated frequently with reviews and videos of some of the equipment they sell. For delivery  there are two options: picking up or have it shipped to you.\r\n\r\n## Shipping\r\nIn an effort to provide best possible prices on ATV trailers in Canada they have worked out the following shipping structure: Shipping to most locations in Canada is free,  ATV Trailers reserve the right to select the carrier: Canada Post, UPS, Fedex, Freight, or local delivery service in the GTA.\r\nShipping is free to most locations but not all. Excluded are Newfoundland, NWT, Yukon, and Nunavut. However they  reserve the right to refuse free shipping to any other location if it''s remote at their discretion (e.g. rural areas, northern BC, northern Quebec etc.). In that case, they can provide you with a shipping quote; they will only ask you to pay the amount which is above the regular shipping rate.\r\n\r\n## Pickup\r\nThis is a great option if you wish to save and also get your trailer quicker and safer. Pickups are available from our partner warehouse in Mississauga, Ontario ( near Steeles Ave. and Bramalea) You''ll still need to make your order through the website, but they offer a discount on all trailers if you are picking up, just check the pickup option at checkout and discount will be applied when you order. Note: they''ll need at least one business day to have your trailer ready for pick up, and this option is only available when paying by credit card, not PayPal.\r\nReturns to ATVTrailers are accepted within 14 days of delivery or pick up date, as recorded by the carrier''s online tracking system.\r\nATVTrailers sells several types of trailers, implements and ramps by quality manufactures, these include:\r\n\r\n## Manufactures \r\n\r\n### Ohio Steel Industries\r\nFounded in 1958, Ohio Steel Industries has been synonymous with high quality commercial products and workmanship. Starting with a 25,000 square foot facility as a structural steel fabricator serving the central Ohio area, Ohio Steel Industries has expanded over the years and today offers products and services in five areas: Structural Steel Fabrication, Plastic Extrusion, Contract Manufacturing, Lawn and Garden equipment, and trailers.\r\n\r\nThey are AISC-certified in Structural Steel Fabrication, and are a recognized leader fabricating, furnishing and erecting structural steel. Their experienced tradesmen take great pride in seeing and knowing they have put their mark and workmanship on buildings, bridges, and structures throughout central Ohio, the Midwest, and the United States. We fabricate, paint, furnish, and erect structural steel buildings, bridges, platforms, and steel structures for widely recognized publicly traded and privately held general contractors, construction managers and owners throughout the United States.\r\n\r\nIn Plastic Extrusion they are a ISO 9001:2008 registered OSI Plastics business and is a recognized leader in plastic extrusion marketplace, providing extrusion services across an array of polymer materials. They provide "complete product" extrusion services including in-line and secondary operations, cutting, bending, notching, drilling, punching, assembling, and packaging. OSI Plastics extrudes polymers profiles for widely recognized publicly traded and privately held brand names throughout the United States and Europe.\r\n\r\nUnder Contract Manufacturing, Ohio Steel researches, designs, develops, engineers, manufactures, and sells diversified lines of OEM and private products and they provide contract manufacturing services for others. They provide fabrication and contract manufacturing services including stamping, forming, bending,  welding, punching, powder coating, assembling, packaging, and shipping.\r\n\r\nOhio Steel manufactures a variety of high-quality lawn and garden and ATV attachments available at retailers and power equipment dealers worldwide. From their line of innovative swivel dump carts to premium lawn sweepers, every item they offer is designed from the ground up with the consumer in mind. Their unique combination of innovation, quality and performance will help get the job done faster and easier and ensure years of worry-free use.\r\n\r\nItems include: Carts, Rollers, Sweepers, Aerators and Dethatchers, Spreaders, ATV Carts, Lifts and Ramps.\r\nAll trailer models are American-made and constructed of tubular steel main frames, cross member and side rails for extreme durability.\r\n[ATVTrailers.ca](http://ATVTrailers.ca) sells a number of Ohio Steel''s ATV products.\r\n\r\n### Ardisam / Yutrax\r\nArdisam has two ATV brands: **Yutrax** and **Rush Ramps**. [ATVTrailers.ca](http://ATVTrailers.ca) sells a number of Yutrax products including ATV trailers, ramps and accessories.\r\nLoading ramps include arch ramps, folding arch ramps, bi-fold and tri-fold ramps all made from aluminum. \r\n\r\nFor trailers they offer the Yutrax X2 trailer and Yutrax X4 steel-mesh utility trailers that will let you tackle large hauling loads.\r\nAccessories include the 2-inch Ball Hitch Kit. With Yutrax’s ball hitch kit you’ll be able to convert Yutrax ATV trailers from a pin-style hitch to a 2-inch ball hitch. Easy to install, all hardware is included.\r\n\r\nThey also have a Tracking Beam Kit that adds stability over rough terrain with the tracking beam kit. It converts any two-wheeled Yutrax trailer to a heavy-duty four-wheeled version with  pivoting attachment arms make for less bounce and a smoother tow.\r\n\r\nThe YuTrax X4 trailer is the only item that must ship via Freight. If you are in Toronto, shipping to you is free. For other locations we normally ship it to a freight terminal near you and you will need to pick up from the terminal. If you need shipping to house please contact us and we will check the rate; where possible it will still be free.\r\n\r\n### MotoAlliance / Impact Implements\r\nMotoAlliance has a line of hitched products under the **Impact Implements** brand that [ATVTrailers.ca](http://ATVTrailers.ca) sells. Some of these products include rakes, point lifts, trailers, weight trays and others.\r\n\r\n[ATVTrailers.ca](http://ATVTrailers.ca) are authorized resellers for every item they carry which means when you buy from them your purchase is under warranty.\r\nVisit [ATVTrailers.ca](http://ATVTrailers.ca) today to see what''s available to meet your needs.', 0, 6, 20, 0, 1, NULL, 'Canada is big and so are ATV trailers which means shipping from USA is expensive and time-consuming, so ATVtrailers keep stock in Canada and thereby provide supplies to Canadians quickly and at great prices.', 'Staff', '', '2016-10-10 23:59:33', '2016-10-11 00:01:27'),
(215, 'GardenCart.ca Online Store for Garden Cart, Gorilla Carts and more in Canada', 'gardencart-ca-online-store-for-garden-cart-gorilla-carts-and-more-in-canada', 'GardenCart Store for Garden Carts, Gorilla Carts', 'GardenCart have a selection of favoured carts which are indestructible, collapsible, lightweight, and multi-purpose.', '', 'GardenCart.ca is an online business who have tried to put together a selection of practical, durable, reasonably priced, and high performance garden carts and wagons for Canadian customers. They have picked carts which are indestructible, collapsible, lightweight, and multi-purpose. They combine these virtues with free shipping in most of Canada!', '[GardenCart.ca](http://GardenCart.ca) is an online business who have tried to put together a selection of practical, durable, reasonably priced, and high performance garden carts and wagons for Canadian customers. They have favoured carts which are indestructible, collapsible, lightweight, and multi-purpose. They combine these virtues with free shipping in most of Canada!\r\n\r\nTheir website is updated frequently with reviews and videos of some of the [garden carts](http://GardenCart.ca) they sell. \r\n\r\n[GardenCart.ca](http://GardenCart.ca) are authorized re-sellers for the garden carts and accessories they carry, which means when you buy from them your purchase is under warranty.\r\n\r\n[GardenCart.ca](http://GardenCart.ca) sells several types of garden carts and accessories by quality manufactures, these include:\r\n\r\n## Manufactures \r\n\r\n### Ohio Steel Industries\r\nFounded in 1958, Ohio Steel Industries has been synonymous with high quality commercial products and workmanship. Starting with a 25,000 square foot facility as a structural steel fabricator serving the central Ohio area, Ohio Steel Industries has expanded over the years and today offers products and services in five areas: Structural Steel Fabrication, Plastic Extrusion, Contract Manufacturing, Lawn and Garden equipment, and trailers.\r\n\r\nOhio Steel manufactures a variety of high-quality lawn and garden carts available at retailers and power equipment dealers worldwide. Every item they offer is designed from the ground up with the consumer in mind. All trailer models are American-made and constructed of tubular steel main frames, cross member and side rails for extreme durability. [GardenCart.ca](http://GardenCart.ca) sells a number of Ohio Steel''s Dump Carts.\r\n\r\n### Muller''s Smart Carts\r\nAs with all great products, the original Muller’s Smart Cart was created out of need for something better.In 1975, Brigadier General Henry Muller of Santa Barbara, California was presented with a problem: His wife who was in her 60’s, was unable to manage a wheelbarrow in their stable without it tilting and causing back pain. Because he knew how much his wife loved her stable work, Henry Muller created the first easy-to-use, lightweight, durable and well balanced stable cart on the market. He patented his new product the Muller’s Stablemate and began selling his design at nearby stables and ranches.\r\n\r\nThough the company’s name has changed throughout the years from Muller’s Town and Country Cart to Smart Cart to Carr Industries to Muller''s Smart Carts of Maine, to Muller’s Carts and finally to Smart Carts Enterprises LLC, the product’s original design remains practically unchanged. Brigadier General Muller’s original design has been shown time and again to withstand heavy use for decades with little to no need for maintenance or repair.Their carts are found at the White House, Walt Disney’s Landscaping Departments, many Zoos including the San Diego Zoo, at MGM Studios, The Hearst Castle, at Strybing Arboretum and beyond. Today, they are based out in Gorham, Maine (near Portland) making the same quality carts that began in 1975. They use local suppliers for parts beyond their capabilities.\r\n\r\nThese legendary carts are designed with ergonomics and ease of movement in mind. These carts are made from durable plastics and steel and come with A lifetime warranty on the frame and a 5-year warranty on the tub.\r\n\r\n[GardenCart.ca](http://GardenCart.ca) sells a number of Muller''s products, see the [website](http://GardenCart.ca) for details.\r\n\r\n### Gorilla Carts from Tricam Industries\r\nAt Gorilla Carts, their mission is to design and engineer products that exceed the highest expectations and their team prides itself on the products and the strong relationships with customers they have maintained from the start. A market leader in lawn and garden carts for over 20 years, every item offered has been engineered and optimized by their US engineering team to deliver an exceptional experience. A relentless focus on innovation and quality ensures you can continue to count on Gorilla Carts to help you get your job done easier, have more fun, and accomplish more. \r\n\r\nGorilla Carts is part of Tricam Industries, a privately-held company headquartered in Eden Prairie, Minnesota, just outside of Minneapolis and includes one of their distribution and warehouse facilities as well as their product development and prototyping shop.\r\n\r\n### Fold-It Carts by Tipke Manufacturing Company\r\nTipke Manufacturing Company, Inc. has been dedicated to producing quality metal goods for over 40 years. All parts are fabricated to the standard and preciseness that customers require and have come to expect from them. \r\n\r\nThe Fold it cart is the best aluminium cart out there for gardening, boating, and marine applications. Made in Washington, USA, these wagons became super famous for their low weight, 20" (50cm) wheels, manoeuvrability, and stability over any terrain. Hardly any effort is required to move the cart with a 330lb (150kg) load on it. Once folded the carts require less than 2 sf storage space. Due to its light weight and small footprint when folded this is a perfect boating cart. These carts are super easy to clean because they are all aluminium - just use a garden hose and do not worry about any rust: the high-grade marine aluminium construction is completely rust and corrosion resistant, even after years of exposure to salt water.\r\n\r\n[GardenCart.ca](http://GardenCart.ca) sells a number of the Fold-It Carts including Industrial Foldit Carts and accessories like the Bicycle Hitch Trailer Hitch, half-height and full-height rear gates.\r\n\r\n### Reels on Wheels by CPI Designs\r\nCPI Designs is an American manufacturing company that produces welded aluminum products for the sporting goods industry, including the Reels on Wheels brand fishing carts, Beagle & Bird dog boxes, and Easy Step folding ladders, as well as accessories. [GardenCart.ca](http://GardenCart.ca) sells a number of the Reels on Wheels fishing carts. \r\n\r\n## Shipping\r\nFor delivery there are two options: picking up your garden cart or have it shipped to you. In an effort to provide best possible prices on garden carts, shipping to most locations in Canada is free, GardenCart reserve the right to select the carrier: Canada Post, UPS, Fedex, Freight, or local delivery service in the GTA.\r\n\r\nShipping is free to most locations but not all. Excluded are Newfoundland, NWT, Yukon, and Nunavut. However they  reserve the right to refuse free shipping to any other location if it''s remote at their discretion (e.g. rural areas, northern BC, northern Quebec etc.). In that case, they can provide you with a shipping quote; they will only ask you to pay the amount which is above the regular shipping rate. Returns to GardenCart are accepted within 14 days of delivery or pick up date, as recorded by the carrier''s online tracking system.\r\n\r\n## Pickup\r\nThis is a great option if you wish to save and also get your trailer quicker and safer. Pickups are available from our partner warehouse in Mississauga, Ontario ( near Steeles Ave. and Bramalea) You''ll still need to make your order through the website, but they offer a discount on all trailers if you are picking up, just check the pickup option at checkout and discount will be applied when you order. Note: they''ll need at least one business day to have your trailer ready for pick up, and this option is only available when paying by credit card, not PayPal.\r\n\r\n\r\nLove gardening? But not breaking your back? Then visit [GardenCart.ca](http://GardenCart.ca) today for the cart just for you.', 0, 20, 6, 0, 1, NULL, 'GardenCart.ca is an online business who have tried to put together a selection of practical, durable, reasonably priced, and high performance garden carts and wagons for Canadian customers. They have favoured carts which are indestructible, collapsible, lightweight, and multi-purpose. They combine these virtues with free shipping in most of Canada!', 'Staff', '', '2016-10-11 02:24:32', '2016-10-11 02:27:43'),
(216, 'How Post-Secondary Students Can Reduce Their Tax Bills', 'how-post-secondary-students-can-reduce-their-tax-bills', 'How Post-Secondary Students Can Reduce Their Tax Bills', 'Think about the credits and deductions available to students on tax bills since changes were announced in the last federal budget. ', '', 'Think about the credits and deductions available to students on tax bills since changes were announced in the last federal budget. ', 'Post-secondary students are back in school this month and are pondering about the credits and deductions available on their tax bills ever since changes have been announced in the federal budget.  \r\n\r\nStudents pursuing their higher education can claim three tax credits that will help them bring down their tax bills. They can claim their tuition, education and textbook credits. Tuition credit is a non-refundable credit, it is worth around 15 percent of the amount of tuition fees and doesn’t have a maximum claim amount. Education amount is 15 percent on $400 for each month of full time education or $120 a month if the student is part time. Text book credits are also similar, they are only available to those who claim the education amount and is worth $9.75 a month for full time students and $3 a month for part time post-secondary students. \r\n\r\nIf the student doesn’t use the credit in a particular year due to lack of sufficient income to claim the credits, the student’s partner, spouse, parent or grandparents can claim it. If there is a remaining amount it can also be used by the student at a future time as a carry-forward credit. \r\n\r\nFrom January 1 education and text credits will be eliminated according to the budget statement. Tuition credit and the carry forward rules will apply have not yet claimed their previous credits that arose before 2017.\r\n\r\nInterest on student loans can be claimed as a non-refundable tax credit, however the interest must be paid by student and not by a parent or someone else. If a student has no tax payable, either because of sufficient credits to pay no tax at all or due to low income then they can carry forward the interest paid and claim it in the following five years. \r\n\r\nStudent loans have to be under the Canada Student Loans Act, the Canada Student Financial Assistance Act or a similar provincial or territorial government law to qualify for the credit.\r\n\r\nThe goods and services tax (GST) can benefit students as it is available to lower-income Canadians who are at least 19; this ensures Post-secondary students are eligible to avail it. A tax return must be filed if a student wishes to utilize this.\r\n \r\nFull time post-secondary students who move at least 40 kilometres to attend the program can also deduct any moving expenses from income earned from part time jobs. Moving for summer jobs is also eligible for deductions since a student who has moved at least 40 kilometers from school during the summer months can deduct the moving costs incurred.', 0, 10, 0, 0, 1, NULL, 'Think about the credits and deductions available to students on tax bills since changes were announced in the last federal budget.', 'Staff', '', '2016-10-11 02:38:10', '2016-10-11 02:38:10'),
(217, 'See Toronto and Vancouver in a New Way With Airbnb''s Guidebooks', 'see-toronto-and-vancouver-with-airbnbs-guidebooks', 'Discover Toronto and Vancouver With Airbnb''s Guidebooks', 'This year visitors to Vancouver and Toronto have a new way to see the cities: Airbnb’s Guidebooks letting guests live like locals.', '', 'This year visitors to Vancouver and Toronto have a new way to see the cities: Airbnb’s Guidebooks, part of a new strategy to get guests to live like locals and avoid the tourist pitfalls. ', 'This year visitors to Vancouver and Toronto have a new way to see cities: Airbnb’s [Guidebooks](https://www.airbnb.ca/things-to-do/). In Canada they have [Vancouver](https://www.airbnb.ca/things-to-do/vancouver), [Toronto](https://www.airbnb.ca/things-to-do/toronto) and Montreal covered with several thousand places listed. This is part of a new strategy to get guests to live like locals and avoid the tourist pitfalls. Airbnb describes the guides as “passports” to places from locals (or other members who have visited the area). This does put Airbnb into competition with services like TripAdvisor and Yelp and it’s still unknown if members will be interested enough in the service to continue using Airbnb apps throughout their trips.\r\n\r\nWorldwide, the Guidebooks started with 3 million tips from 23 of the most popular cities on Airbnb: Austin, Bangkok, Barcelona, Berlin, Boston, Buenos Aires, Lake Tahoe, London, Los Angeles, Melbourne, Mexico City, Miami, New York, Paris, Rio de Janeiro, Rome, San Francisco, Seoul, Sydney, Tel Aviv, Tokyo, Venice and Washington, DC.\r\n\r\nRelated to this is the the neighbourhood feature works. It covers around 690 specific areas within 23 cities, the idea is to try to introduce visitors to more areas that they might not have considered.\r\n\r\n>>> ### “The number one reason people chose to travel on Airbnb is they want to live like a local. They don’t want to be tourists stuck in long lines, fighting with the crowds to see the same thing as everyone else,” <small>- Brian Chesky, Airbnb co-founder/CEO</small>\r\n\r\nAs well, as travelers look at individual listings, Airbnb’s machine learning models come up with additional places people might like that are similar, based on factors like room types, number of guests, price ranges, and number of times you visit a listing, to come up with additional places you might be interested in based on what you’re looking for. They say that with several months testing, they’ve seen a dramatic increase in successful bookings.\r\n\r\nThe technology behind this comes from Trip4Real, a company that Airbnb had partnered with for several years and acquired in September 2016. Trip4Real is a travel-focused startup from Barcelona whose business model was built on offering activities in cities around the world. Its slogan "experience a city like a local" sounds like the message Airbnb has been pushing for some time now. Trip4Real website promised visitors thousands of local experiences that were "made by locals" in cities around the world with the goal of helping travelers find things off the beaten path. This meshed with Airbnb’s vision to help travelers avoid cookie-cutter trips by including locally-sourced info about neighbourhoods, something that started to show up when it launched redesigned apps earlier this year. \r\n\r\nBack in October 2015, Airbnb started testing “Journeys” a way to pick a city and let the company book accommodations and pair that with meals, transportation and a local host to show you around town. This lead to apps like the short-lived Airbnb Trips app for Android, and work continues on integrating human expertise and machine-learning. \r\n\r\nAs well as this, Airbnb is exploring other ways to use local knowledge to combat potential problems, such as the new feedback tool that is coming out this year, it allows neighbours of Airbnb properties to comment on the behavior of guests, as a way of combating ''party houses''.\r\n\r\nFor your next visit to [Toronto](https://www.airbnb.ca/things-to-do/toronto) or [Vancouver](https://www.airbnb.ca/things-to-do/vancouver), consider checking out Airbnb’s new guidebooks, you might find some unexpected gems.', 0, 11, 20, 0, 1, NULL, 'This year visitors to Vancouver and Toronto have a new way to see the cities: Airbnb’s Guidebooks, part of a new strategy to get guests to live like locals and avoid the tourist pitfalls.', 'Staff', '', '2016-10-21 04:31:37', '2016-10-21 04:35:09');
